{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775890948565,"sessionID":"ses_284a83a8fffe4tt8aAyvzY88X6","part":{"id":"prt_d7b5961ad001gq5u1q1l0Hoapm","messageID":"msg_d7b595520001th2u7TYe1iTHR8","sessionID":"ses_284a83a8fffe4tt8aAyvzY88X6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-2914b8197963460b85cdcffe2f652bb8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/examples/pcap-analyzer/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/examples/pcap-analyzer/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PCAP Analyzer\n2: \n3: A comprehensive PCAP (packet capture) analysis example application demonstrating the AgentCube Python SDK.\n4: \n5: ## Overview\n6: \n7: This example application demonstrates how to use the AgentCube SDK to:\n8: \n9: - Upload PCAP files to a Code Interpreter session\n10: - Install and configure PCAP analysis libraries (scapy, pyshark, matplotlib, pandas)\n11: - Perform comprehensive network traffic analysis\n12: - Generate visualizations and reports\n13: - Download results to your local machine\n14: \n15: ## Features\n16: \n17: ### Analysis Capabilities\n18: \n19: - **Basic Statistics**: Packet count, protocol distribution, time range analysis\n20: - **Top Talkers**: Top source/destination IPs by packet and byte count, bidirectional traffic\n21: - **Port Analysis**: Top source/destination ports with service mapping\n22: - **HTTP Traffic**: Request/response analysis, status codes, top hosts\n23: - **DNS Traffic**: Query analysis, domain statistics, response types, failure detection\n24: - **Visualizations**: Protocol distribution pie charts, packets over time graphs, top IPs bar charts\n25: - **Report Generation**: Markdown and HTML reports with embedded visualizations\n26: \n27: ### Architecture\n28: \n29: ```\n30: pcap_analyzer_example.py\n31:     ├── CodeInterpreterClient\n32:     │   ├── EnvironmentSetup (library installation)\n33:     │   ├── FileUploader (PCAP file upload)\n34:     │   ├── PacketStatistics (basic analysis)\n35:     │   ├── TopTalkersAnalyzer (IP analysis)\n36:     │   ├── PortAnalyzer (port analysis)\n37:     │   ├── TrafficVisualizer (charts/graphs)\n38:     │   ├── HTTPAnalyzer (HTTP traffic)\n39:     │   ├── DNSAnalyzer (DNS traffic)\n40:     │   └── ReportGenerator (report creation)\n41:     └── PCAPAnalyzer (main integration class)\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ## Installation\n45: \n46: ### Prerequisites\n47: \n48: - Python 3.10+\n49: - AgentCube deployment with Router and Workload Manager services\n50: - Working `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` installation\n51: \n52: ### Install Dependencies\n53: \n54: ```bash\n55: pip install -r requirements.txt\n56: ```\n57: \n58: ## Configuration\n59: \n60: ### Required Environment Variables\n61: \n62: | Variable | Description | Example |\n63: |----------|-------------|---------|\n64: | `ROUTER_URL` | AgentCube Router service URL | `http://localhost:8080` |\n65: \n66: ### Optional Environment Variables\n67: \n68: | Variable | Description | Default |\n69: |----------|-------------|---------|\n70: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload Manager service URL | None |\n71: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | Code Interpreter session name | `pcap-analyzer` |\n72: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | Kubernetes namespace | `default` |\n73: | `SANDBOX_TTL` | Session time-to-live (seconds) | `3600` |\n74: \n75: ## Usage\n76: \n77: ### Basic Usage\n78: \n79: ```bash\n80: python pcap_analyzer_example.py \\\n81:     --router-url http://localhost:8080 \\\n82:     --local-pcap-path /path/to/capture.pcap \\\n83:     --remote-pcap-path /tmp/capture.pcap \\\n84:     --output-format markdown\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ### Command-Line Arguments\n88: \n89: | Argument | Required | Default | Description |\n90: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n91: | `--router-url` | Yes | - | AgentCube Router URL |\n92: | `--workload-manager-url` | No | - | Workload Manager URL |\n93: | `--name` | No | `pcap-analyzer` | Session name |\n94: | `--namespace` | No | `default` | Kubernetes namespace |\n95: | `--ttl` | No | `3600` | Session TTL (seconds) |\n96: | `--local-pcap-path` | Yes | - | Local PCAP file path |\n97: | `--remote-pcap-path` | No | `/tmp/capture.pcap` | Remote file path |\n98: | `--output-dir` | No | `output` | Local output directory |\n99: | `--remote-output-dir` | No | `/tmp/pcap_analysis` | Remote output directory |\n100: | `--output-format` | No | `markdown` | Report format (markdown/html) |\n101: | `--verbose` | No | `false` | Enable verbose logging |\n102: \n103: ### Programmatic Usage\n104: \n105: ```python\n106: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n107: from src.pcap_analyzer import PCAPAnalyzer\n108: \n109: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n110:     router_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n111:     name=\"pcap-analyzer\",\n112:     verbose=True,\n113: ) as client:\n114:     analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(client)\n115:     \n116:     analyzer.setup_environment()\n117:     analyzer.upload_file(\"/local/capture.pcap\", \"/remote/capture.pcap\")\n118:     \n119:     results = analyzer.analyze_pcap_file(\"/remote/capture.pcap\")\n120:     \n121:     analyzer.generate_report(results, \"/remote/report.md\", \"markdown\")\n122:     analyzer.download_file(\"/remote/report.md\", \"local/report.md\")\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ## API Reference\n126: \n127: ### PCAPAnalyzer\n128: \n129: Main class integrating all analysis modules.\n130: \n131: #### Methods\n132: \n133: - `setup_environment() -> bool`: Install required libraries\n134: - `upload_file(local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> str`: Upload PCAP file\n135: - `analyze_pcap_file(remote_path: str, output_dir: str = \"/tmp/pcap_analysis\", generate_visualizations: bool = True) -> Dict`: Run all analyses\n136: - `generate_report(analysis_results: Dict, output_path: str, format: str = \"markdown\") -> str`: Generate report\n137: - `download_file(remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None`: Download file\n138: \n139: ### Analysis Modules\n140: \n141: #### EnvironmentSetup\n142: - `setup_scapy()`: Install scapy library\n143: - `setup_pyshark()`: Install pyshark library\n144: - `setup_visualization_libs()`: Install matplotlib and pandas\n145: - `verify_installation() -> bool`: Verify all libraries installed\n146: - `setup_all() -> bool`: Install all libraries\n147: \n148: #### PacketStatistics\n149: - `analyze_packet_count(remote_path: str) -> int`: Count total packets\n150: - `analyze_protocols(remote_path: str) -> Dict`: Analyze protocol distribution\n151: - `analyze_time_range(remote_path: str) -> Tuple`: Calculate time range\n152: \n153: #### TopTalkersAnalyzer\n154: - `analyze_top_source_ips(remote_path: str, limit: int = 10) -> List`: Top source IPs\n155: - `analyze_top_destination_ips(remote_path: str, limit: int = 10) -> List`: Top destination IPs\n156: - `analyze_top_ips_by_bytes(remote_path: str, limit: int = 10) -> List`: Top IPs by bytes\n157: - `analyze_bidirectional_traffic(remote_path: str) -> Dict`: Bidirectional traffic\n158: \n159: #### PortAnalyzer\n160: - `analyze_top_source_ports(remote_path: str, limit: int = 10) -> List`: Top source ports\n161: - `analyze_top_destination_ports(remote_path: str, limit: int = 10) -> List`: Top destination ports\n162: - `analyze_ports_with_services(remote_path: str) -> List`: Ports with service mapping\n163: - `filter_by_port(remote_path: str, port: int) -> Dict`: Filter by port\n164: \n165: #### HTTPAnalyzer\n166: - `analyze_http_requests(remote_path: str) -> List`: Extract HTTP requests\n167: - `analyze_http_responses(remote_path: str) -> List`: Extract HTTP responses\n168: - `analyze_http_status_codes(remote_path: str) -> Dict`: Count status codes\n169: - `analyze_top_http_hosts(remote_path: str, limit: int = 10) -> List`: Top hosts\n170: \n171: #### DNSAnalyzer\n172: - `analyze_dns_queries(remote_path: str) -> List`: Extract DNS queries\n173: - `analyze_top_dns_domains(remote_path: str, limit: int = 10) -> List`: Top domains\n174: - `analyze_dns_response_types(remote_path: str) -> Dict`: Response types\n175: - `analyze_dns_failures(remote_path: str) -> List`: DNS failures\n176: \n177: #### TrafficVisualizer\n178: - `visualize_protocol_distribution(protocol_data: Dict, output_path: str) -> str`: Generate pie chart\n179: - `visualize_packets_over_time(remote_path: str, output_path: str) -> str`: Generate line chart\n180: - `visualize_top_ips(ip_data: List, title: str, output_path: str) -> str`: Generate bar chart\n181: \n182: #### ReportGenerator\n183: - `generate_report(analysis_results: Dict, output_path: str, format: str) -> str`: Generate report\n184: - `generate_markdown_report(analysis_results: Dict, output_path: str) -> str`: Generate markdown report\n185: - `generate_html_report(analysis_results: Dict, output_path: str) -> str`: Generate HTML report\n186: - `add_metadata(analysis_results: Dict, file_name: str) -> Dict`: Add metadata\n187: \n188: ## Testing\n189: \n190: Run all tests:\n191: \n192: ```bash\n193: pytest\n194: ```\n195: \n196: Run tests with coverage:\n197: \n198: ```bash\n199: pytest --cov=src --cov-report=html\n200: ```\n201: \n202: Run specific test file:\n203: \n204: ```bash\n205: pytest tests/test_pcap_analyzer.py -v\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ## Sample PCAP File\n209: \n210: A sample PCAP file is provided at `tests/sample.pcap` for testing purposes. It contains:\n211: \n212: - TCP traffic on ports 80 and 443\n213: - UDP DNS traffic\n214: - ICMP packets\n215: - Multiple source and destination IP addresses\n216: \n217: ## Troubleshooting\n218: \n219: ### Connection Issues\n220: \n221: If you cannot connect to the AgentCube services:\n222: \n223: 1. Verify `ROUTER_URL` is correct\n224: 2. Check that Router and Workload Manager services are running\n225: 3. Ensure network connectivity to the services\n226: \n227: ### Library Installation Failures\n228: \n229: If library installation fails:\n230: \n231: 1. Check internet connectivity in the sandbox environment\n232: 2. Verify pip is available in the sandbox\n233: 3. Try installing libraries manually with increased timeout\n234: \n235: ### Memory Issues with Large PCAP Files\n236: \n237: For large PCAP files (>100MB):\n238: \n239: 1. Increase session TTL\n240: 2. Process files in chunks if needed\n241: 3. Monitor memory usage during analysis\n242: \n243: ### Timeout Errors\n244: \n245: If operations timeout:\n246: \n247: 1. Increase timeout values in the code\n248: 2. Check if the PCAP file is very large\n249: 3. Verify the sandbox has sufficient resources\n250: \n251: ## Performance Characteristics\n252: \n253: | File Size | Expected Duration | Memory Usage |\n254: |-----------|------------------|--------------|\n255: | < 10 MB | < 30 seconds | Low |\n256: | 10-100 MB | 30-300 seconds | Medium |\n257: | > 100 MB | 5-15 minutes | High |\n258: \n259: ## License\n260: \n261: This example is part of the AgentCube project.\n262: \n263: ## Contributing\n264: \n265: This is an example application. For contributions to the main AgentCube project, please refer to the main repository.\n\n(End of file - total 265 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PCAP Analyzer\n\nA comprehensive PCAP (packet capture) analysis example application demonstrating the AgentCube Python SDK.\n\n## Overview\n\nThis example application demonstrates how to use the AgentCube SDK to:\n\n- Upload PCAP files to a Code Interpreter session\n- Install and configure PCAP analysis libraries (scapy, pyshark, matplotlib, pandas)\n- Perform comprehensive network traffic analysis\n- Generate visualizations and reports\n- Download results to your local machine\n\n## Features\n\n### Analysis Capabilities\n\n- **Basic Statistics**: Packet count, protocol distribution, time range analysis\n- **Top Talkers**: Top source/destination IPs by packet and byte count, bidirectional traffic","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/examples/pcap-analyzer/README.md","time":{"start":1775890948558,"end":1775890948563}}}}
